This workshop will address the challenges and benefits of grid interoperability at the international, national, and campus levels. The workshop will consist of three panels of experts, one from each of these domains. The panelists will discuss issues in: authentication and authorization, security, scheduling resources, standards and protocols, policies and procedures for interoperation, research directions, challenges to interoperation/interoperability, cechnical approaches to achieving interoperation/interoperability, and science and education community requirements.